p: The compounds identified from the A. graveolens EO by GC-MS are listed in Table S1. All components of A. graveolens contain volatile oils, and their compositions are different depending on the vegetative/reproductive organ from which the extraction is carried out [ 21]. According to Rădulescu et al. (2010), the main components of the volatile oil extracted from the leaves of A. graveolens are α-felandren, limonene, and dill ether [ 22]. In our study, α-phellandrene (68.541%) and β-phellandrene (9.431%) were the main components identified in the A. graveolens EO.
